{"title": "Article 2346", "body": {"ops": [{"insert": "Digital stabilization of unstable equilibria of linear systems may lead to small amplitude stochastic-like oscillations. We show that these vibrations can be related to a deterministic chaotic dynamics induced by sampling and quantization. A detailed analytical proof of chaos is presented for the case of a PD controlled oscillator: it is shown that there exists a finite attracting domain in the phase-space, the largest Lyapunov exponent is positive and the existence of a Smale horseshoe is also pointed out. The corresponding two-dimensional micro-chaos map is a multi-baker map, i.e. it consists of a finite series of baker's maps.\n"}]}, "text": "Digital stabilization of unstable equilibria of linear systems may lead to small amplitude stochastic-like oscillations. We show that these vibrations can be related to a deterministic chaotic dynamics induced by sampling and quantization. A detailed analytical proof of chaos is presented for the case of a PD controlled oscillator: it is shown that there exists a finite attracting domain in the phase-space, the largest Lyapunov exponent is positive and the existence of a Smale horseshoe is also pointed out. The corresponding two-dimensional micro-chaos map is a multi-baker map, i.e. it consists of a finite series of baker's maps.\n", "updatedAt": 1714670437, "embeddings": ["0.98024476", "-0.6417213", "0.21251473", "-0.29017198", "-0.49640524", "-0.40479067", "0.55501807", "1.110123", "0.54867643", "-1.1437659", "-0.1666077", "-0.85363317", "0.32233593", "0.09302424", "-1.2320447", "0.56409764", "1.5023668", "-0.022712287", "0.15862402", "-0.03175923", "0.7138158", "-0.009877304", "0.38513702", "0.35281587", "-1.3815824", "1.4251113", "0.43099588", "0.72646505", "0.9771807", "-0.9390216", "1.1812096", "0.4670975", "0.4793983", "-0.5478558", "-0.7442529", "-0.9466797", "-0.60333645", "0.52058923", "-0.59895116", "0.73680556", "-0.7714796", "0.76062274", "-0.50745904", "-0.